-- IMF sees Polish govt deficit falling to 2.5 pct of GDP in 2015 -source
-- By Pawel Sobczak
-- Wed May 14, 2014 04:30AM EDT
-- None



WARSAW, May 14 (Reuters) - The International Monetary Fund (IMF) sees Poland's general government deficit falling to 2.5 percent of the country's Gross Domestic Product (GDP) in 2015 from the 3.3 percent it expects for this year, according to a person who saw the IMF forecast.

The IMF forecast is in line with the Polish government's expectations, according to which the deficit is set to fall to 2.5 percent next year.